## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="296df-109"><xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Abandon%2A> może zostać zawieszone, gdy istnieje transakcja otoczenia i <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Complete%2A> nosi nazwę, a następnie transakcja zostanie wycofana.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="296df-109"><xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Abandon%2A> may hang when there is an ambient transaction and <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Complete%2A> is called and afterwards the transaction is rolled back.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="296df-110">Jeśli <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Abandon%2A> jest wywoływana przed ukończeniu wycofywania transakcji, wyścigu będzie istnieć, co powoduje wywołanie <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Abandon%2A> zawieszenie.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="296df-110">If <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Abandon%2A> is called prior to the transaction rollback completing, a race condition will exist, causing the call to <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Abandon%2A> to hang.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="296df-111">To może zilustrowane w poniższym przykładzie pseudo-kodu</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="296df-111">This can be illustrated by the following pseudo-code example</span></span>  
  
```  
using (TransactionScope ts = new TransactionScope())   
{  
   try  
   {  
       rc.Complete();  
      ...  
   }  
   Catch (Exception)   
   {  
      rc.Abandon()  
   }  
}  
  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="296df-112">Nie jest zalecane wzorzec do pracy z T:System.ServiceModel.Channels.RecieveContext.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="296df-112">This is not the recommended pattern for working with T:System.ServiceModel.Channels.RecieveContext.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="296df-113">Zamiast tego bloku try/catch powinny być umieszczone poza zasięgiem transakcji.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="296df-113">Instead the try/catch block should be placed outside of the transaction scope.</span></span>

